         <div type="translation">
            <ab>(Latin text, Scriptio interior, Page III);;[- - -];          I, [. . . Cornelius] Iustus, the son of Marcus, whose census rating is 20 (thousand) sesterces, (registered) in the monthly record as a Roman citizen [my son], Marcus Cornelius Iustus, born of [. . .] Heras, daughter of Marcus, on the 4th day before the Ides of September last past.;;;(Latin list of witnesses, Page IV);;(Seals) of Gaius Cornelius Rufus, veteran;                of Marcus Egnatius Longus, veteran;                of Gaius Iulius Valens, veteran;                of Quintus Ancharettius Proculus;[- - -];;(Latin text, Scriptio exterior, Pages IV);;In the consulship of the Emperor Caesar Nerva Trajan Augustus, for the fifth time, and [Marius] Laberius Maximus(?), for the second time(?), [- - -]</ab>
         </div>
